# Controllers e Handler Lambda

## Controller: base class Controller

Todo controller da API deve **estender** a classe `Controller` (`@application/interfaces/controller`), com:

- `protected override schema = ...` (Zod schema; opcional se não houver validação de body)
- `protected override async handle(request: IRequest<SchemaType>): Promise<IResponse>` — passar `userId` e `params` do `request` para o service quando necessário

Não use try/catch nem `errorHandler` no controller; erros são tratados pelo lambda adapter.

**Exemplo (só body):**

```typescript
import { Controller } from "@application/interfaces/controller";
import type { IRequest, IResponse } from "@application/interfaces/http";

export class XController extends Controller {
  constructor(private readonly service: IXService) {
    super();
  }

  protected override schema = mySchema;

  protected override async handle(request: IRequest<MySchemaType>): Promise<IResponse> {
    const result = await this.service.execute(request.body);
    return { statusCode: 200, body: result };
  }
}
```

**Exemplo (service precisa de userId/params):**

```typescript
  protected override async handle(request: IRequest<MySchemaType>): Promise<IResponse> {
    const result = await this.service.execute({
      ...request.body,
      userId: request.userId ?? "",
      projectId: request.params.projectId as string,
    });
    return { statusCode: 200, body: result };
  }
```

## Handler Lambda: lambdaHttpAdapter

Handlers Lambda **não** devem chamar `requestAdapter` nem `responseAdapter` manualmente. Use o adapter único:

- Importe o factory do controller e `lambdaHttpAdapter` de `@server/adapters/lambda-http-adapter`.
- Instancie o controller uma vez e exporte `handler = lambdaHttpAdapter(controller)`.

**Exemplo:**

```typescript
import { makeXController } from "@factories/controllers/<domain>/<feature>";
import { lambdaHttpAdapter } from "@server/adapters/lambda-http-adapter";

const controller = makeXController();
export const handler = lambdaHttpAdapter(controller);
```

O `lambdaHttpAdapter` encapsula: `event` → `requestAdapter` → `controller.execute(request)` (validação + `handle`) → `responseAdapter`; em caso de erro, `errorHandler` formata a resposta.
